        <p>Common questions about Clearscope. More? Email <a href="mailto:founder@thestacc.com">founder@thestacc.com</a>.</p>
        <p style="margin-top: 24px;">See also: <a href="/alternatives/clearscope/" class="accent">Clearscope alternatives</a>, <a href="/modules/content-seo/" class="accent">Content SEO module</a>, or <a href="/pricing/" class="accent">theStacc pricing</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is Clearscope?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Clearscope is a content optimization platform that uses IBM Watson NLP to analyze top-ranking search results and grade your content A+ through F based on topic coverage. It updates in real time as you write inside its editor, Google Docs, or WordPress.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much does Clearscope cost?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Clearscope starts at $129/month for the Essentials plan (or ~$107/month billed annually). The Business plan is $399/month (~$331/month annual). Enterprise pricing is custom. All plans include unlimited users.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is there a free trial for Clearscope?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">No. Clearscope does not offer a free trial. There is a 7-day refund window after you pay — which is not the same thing. Competitors like Frase offer a genuine 7-day trial with no credit card required.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Clearscope write or publish content?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Clearscope has an AI Drafts feature (20 per month) but it generates starting points that need significant editing. It cannot auto-publish to your website. It optimizes content — it doesn't create or distribute it.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is Clearscope worth it for small businesses?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Probably not if you're a solo operator. At $129/month plus the cost of a writer ($80-$250 per article), you're spending $1,700-$5,100/month to publish 20 articles. A done-for-you platform like theStacc publishes 30 articles automatically for $99/month.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Clearscope do local SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">No. Clearscope is focused entirely on website content optimization. There are no Google Business Profile tools, no local citation management, and no Google Maps ranking features.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How does Clearscope compare to Surfer SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Clearscope charges a flat monthly fee regardless of team size. Surfer charges per seat. For a 5-person team, Clearscope costs $25.80/user vs Surfer's $60+/user. Clearscope uses IBM Watson NLP; Surfer uses TF-IDF. They produce different term recommendations and suit different workflows.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the Content Inventory feature in Clearscope?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Content Inventory connects your domain and tracks optimization grades across your indexed pages. It surfaces articles that have drifted below the ranking threshold so you know what to refresh. The Essentials plan covers 50 pages; Business covers 300.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
